In a warmly lit, nostalgic puppet shop, two highly detailed wooden eastern-style dragon marionettes hang from visible, realistically positioned strings. The left half features a large, dominant blue-green dragon with an intense, confident expression, fierce carved brows, and sweeping wooden whiskers. Its body is intricately carved with ornate spiral patterns, jointed limbs, and polished wood grain textures. It exudes authority and elegance.

On the right, a smaller red dragon marionette gazes upward at the larger dragon with wide, submissive yet gentle eyes. The red dragon has a smoother, more delicate carving style, subtle curls in its posture, and a shy, reverent demeanor. Both dragons hang suspended midair by thin, taut strings that attach naturally at their limbs and torso, emphasizing the marionette realism.

The background shows a cozy puppet shop with wooden shelves full of other handcrafted toys, softly blurred to maintain focus on the dragons. Lighting is soft and ambient, casting warm shadows that enhance the rich wooden textures. The entire scene evokes a whimsical but grounded tone, blending craftsmanship with personality.

Style:
Photorealistic, warm indoor lighting, rich woodgrain detailing, handcrafted marionette realism. Inspired by fine woodworking and antique toy displays. Subtle fantasy undertones, no painterly texture, clean and digital clarity.
